personalInfo.education: Jackson State University (1997, Health, Physical Education and Recreation)

tourBios.curYearHigh: Played in six events on the Web.com Tour, missing the cut in all six tournaments.
tourBios.carHigh: 2012: Granted a Minor Medical Extension for the 2013 season. 2011: Played in nine tournaments on the Canadian Tour, making the cut five times. Top finish was a T29 at the Canadian Tour Championship, where he had a pair of 67s in the second and third rounds.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Was a member of his high school state champion 4-by-100 relay team...Attended Kooralbyn International School in Australia in high school...Played on the Canadian Tour in 2011.
tourBios.personal: Worked as an activity director at an adult daycare center after college...Never travels without the Bible. Favorite website is biblegateway.com. Is an Arizona Cardinals fan. Enjoys watching "X Factor." Favorite gadget is his smart phone. Not many people know that he is a professional trick-shot artist

tourBios.otherInfo: Also played on the Gateway Tour in 2011
